Package com.atakmap.map.layer.raster

Class LocalRasterDataStore

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.atakmap.map.layer.raster.AbstractRasterDataStore
      • com.atakmap.map.layer.raster.LocalRasterDataStore
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    RasterDataStore, Disposable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    PersistentRasterDataStore, RuntimeLocalRasterDataStore
    public abstract class LocalRasterDataStore
extends AbstractRasterDataStore
implements RasterDataStore
    A RasterDataStore on the local file system. If modifiable, supports add, remove and update operations making use of DatasetDescriptorFactory. Implementations are responsible for the data structure managing the datasets.

    • Constructor Detail

      • LocalRasterDataStore

        protected LocalRasterDataStore​(java.io.File workingDir)
        Creates a new instance. The specified working directory will contain the working directories for all layers created and managed by the data store. Consistent with the general contract for DatasetDescriptor, any content created in the working directory must be guaranteed to persist so long as the associated DatasetDescriptor object persists.
        Parameters:
        workingDir - The working directory

    • Method Detail

      • beginBatch

        public void beginBatch()
        Begins a batch operation on the data store. Dispatch of content changed notifications will be deferred until the batch is signaled to be complete via endBatch().

      • endBatch

        public void endBatch()
        Ends a batch operation on the data store. Dispatch of content changed notifications will occur if the content in the data store has changed since the previous invocation of beginBatch().

      • addNoSync

        protected boolean addNoSync​(java.io.File file,
                            java.lang.String hint,
                            InteractiveServiceProvider.Callback callback,
                            boolean notify)
                     throws java.io.IOException
        Implementation for add(File, String). Returns true on success.

        Modification of the data store is internally synchronized on this. It is recommended not to invoke this method when externally synchronized on this as creation of the dataset descriptors may take significant time.

        Parameters:
        file - A file
        hint - The provider hint
        notify - If true, dispatchDataStoreContentChangedNoSync() will be invoked prior to this method returning successfully
        Returns:
        true if the layers for the file were added, false if no layers could be derived from the file.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
